When you reset the pose to the initial trajectory pose in getAutonomousCommand, why do you only set the translation and set the rotation to 180 degrees (pi radians):

Pose2d resetPose = new Pose2d(autoTrajectory.getInitialPose().getTranslation(), new Rotation2d(Math.PI));
drivetrain.resetOdometry(resetPose);

Instead of translation and rotation?

drivetrain.resetOdometry(autoTrajectory.getInitialPose());

Also in Robot.java, you reset the translation again, and then reset the gyro position, which could mess up the pose’s angle - when you reset the pose, it offsets for the current gyro value, so if you then reset it it thinks the robot turned.
